Merge pull request #38 from compwron/master

performance improvement
Merge remote-tracking branch 'remotes/jkrall/master'
Spec and fix for parse_raw with short & long input
Include the license type (Apache 2.0) in .gemspec
Fix rake benchmark to work with all travis-ci versions
Fix rake benchmark to work with both 2.1.2 and 1.8.7
Fix UUID::parse_raw correctness, 1.8.7 & ree support
Fix 'benchmark' rake task for Ruby 1.9

Improve performance of parse calls (and Version 4)

Changes:
 + Optimized UUID::parse_raw for approx ~2.5x speedup
 + Optimized UUID::parse_int for approx ~5x speedup
 + Optimized UUID::parse_hexdigest for approx ~3x speedup
 + Optimized UUID::convert_byte_string_to_int for approx 1.5x speedup
    -> Results in Version 4 UUIDs generated at approx 1.4x speedup

Update benchmarks for module, add new benchmarks

It looks like benchmarks haven't been used in awhile since they refer to ::UUID instead of UUIDTools::UUID.
Changes:
 + Fix old benchmarks to work using the latest version for the library.
 + DRY-up benchmark measurement and result formatting
 + Add new benchmarks for parsing and parts of the private api
Preparing for 2.1.5 release.
Updating to the new RSpec syntax.
